      "summary": "Two active workflow-control implementations duplicate shot-association behavior and split one responsibility across parallel UI paths.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/components/WorkflowControlsBar.tsx",
          "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/components/WorkflowControls.tsx",
          "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/components/ShotSelectorControls.tsx",
          "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/components/layouts/LightboxLayout.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`LightboxLayout` renders both control systems depending on layout path (`<WorkflowControlsBar {...props.workflowBar} />` and `<WorkflowControls {...workflowControlsProps} />`).",
          "`WorkflowControlsBar` and `WorkflowControls` both own nearly identical concerns (shot selection, add-with/without-position, apply-settings) and pass many of the same fields.",
          "`ShotSelectorControls` adds another overlapping layer, including its own asynchronous add-variant/add-without-position flows and optimistic UI signaling."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Consolidate into one workflow-controls domain component with layout-specific visual wrappers only; centralize shot-association action state and async flow in a single hook/model consumed by all layouts.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
