      "file": ".",
      "summary": "Lightbox layers add indirection without transformation, inflating interfaces and obscuring ownership.",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "design_coherence",
        "related_files": [
          "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/MediaLightbox.tsx",
          "src/shared/components/MediaGallery/components/MediaGalleryLightbox.tsx",
          "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/presenters/imageLightboxModels.ts",
          "src/shared/components/MediaLightbox/ImageLightbox.tsx"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`MediaGalleryLightbox` decomposes a large `session` object into sub-contracts, then reconstructs another large prop object for `MediaLightbox`.",
          "`MediaLightbox` groups flat props via `useBundledLightboxProps` then dispatches them to `ImageLightbox`/`VideoLightbox`; this is mostly reshaping, not behavior isolation.",
          "`imageLightboxModels.ts` contains no-op wrappers (`buildWorkflowBarModel` and `buildWorkflowControlsModel` both `return input`), indicating ceremony without abstraction leverage."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Replace pass-through layers with a smaller, behavior-oriented lightbox context/model (commands + derived state), and remove no-op presenter wrappers; keep mapping only at true boundary translations.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
