      "file": ".",
      "summary": "Prompt-count loader can return NaN from malformed session storage without fallback",
      "detail": {
        "holistic": true,
        "dimension": "logic_clarity",
        "related_files": [
          "src/shared/components/ImageGenerationForm/hooks/promptManagement/storedPromptCount.ts",
          "src/shared/components/ImageGenerationForm/hooks/usePromptManagement.ts",
          "src/shared/components/ImageGenerationForm/hooks/promptManagement/usePromptPersistenceEffects.ts"
        ],
        "evidence": [
          "`getStoredPromptCount` returns `parseInt(stored, 10)` directly; `parseInt('bad', 10)` yields `NaN`.",
          "`usePromptManagement` uses this value as initial state for `lastKnownPromptCount`.",
          "`usePromptPersistenceEffects` re-reads the same helper and writes derived counts, so invalid numeric state can persist until overwritten."
        ],
        "suggestion": "Clamp helper output to a finite positive integer (`const n = Number.parseInt(...); return Number.isFinite(n) && n > 0 ? n : 1;`) and keep all call sites unchanged.",
        "reasoning": ""
      },
      "status": "open",
